#, no-wrap
msgid "Slots"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 864
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 865
msgid "You will often need to pass additional content to your component via \"slots\". Component slots are rendered by echoing the `$slot` variable. To explore this concept, let's imagine that an `alert` component has the following markup:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 865
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 866
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- /resources/views/components/alert.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-danger\">\n"
"    {{ $slot }}\n"
"</div>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 874
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 875
msgid "We may pass content to the `slot` by injecting content into the component:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 875
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 876
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<x-alert>\n"
"    <strong>Whoops!</strong> Something went wrong!\n"
"</x-alert>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 882
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 883
msgid "Sometimes a component may need to render multiple different slots in different locations within the component. Let's modify our alert component to allow for the injection of a \"title\" slot:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 883
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 884
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- /resources/views/components/alert.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<span class=\"alert-title\">{{ $title }}</span>\n"
"\n"
"<div class=\"alert alert-danger\">\n"
"    {{ $slot }}\n"
"</div>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 894
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 895
msgid "You may define the content of the named slot using the `x-slot` tag. Any content not within an explicit `x-slot` tag will be passed to the component in the `$slot` variable:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 895
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 896
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<x-alert>\n"
"    <x-slot name=\"title\">\n"
"        Server Error\n"
"    </x-slot>\n"
"\n"
"    <strong>Whoops!</strong> Something went wrong!\n"
"</x-alert>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 906
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 907
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"scoped-slots\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 906
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 907
#, no-wrap
msgid "Scoped Slots"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 909
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 910
msgid "If you have used a JavaScript framework such as Vue, you may be familiar with \"scoped slots\", which allow you to access data or methods from the component within your slot. You may achieve similar behavior in Laravel by defining public methods or properties on your component and accessing the component within your slot via the `$component` variable. In this example, we will assume that the `x-alert` component has a public `formatAlert` method defined on its component class:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 910
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 911
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<x-alert>\n"
"    <x-slot name=\"title\">\n"
"        {{ $component->formatAlert('Server Error') }}\n"
"    </x-slot>\n"
"\n"
"    <strong>Whoops!</strong> Something went wrong!\n"
"</x-alert>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 921
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 922
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"slot-attributes\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 921
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 922
#, no-wrap
msgid "Slot Attributes"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 924
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 925
msgid "Like Blade components, you may assign additional [attributes](#component-attributes) to slots such as CSS class names:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 925
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 926
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<x-card class=\"shadow-sm\">\n"
"    <x-slot name=\"heading\" class=\"font-bold\">\n"
"        Heading\n"
"    </x-slot>\n"
"\n"
"    Content\n"
"\n"
"    <x-slot name=\"footer\" class=\"text-sm\">\n"
"        Footer\n"
"    </x-slot>\n"
"</x-card>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 940
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 941
msgid "To interact with slot attributes, you may access the `attributes` property of the slot's variable. For more information on how to interact with attributes, please consult the documentation on [component attributes](#component-attributes):"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Code fence info string
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 941
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 942
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1386
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1394
#, no-wrap
msgid "php"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 941
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 942
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@props([\n"
"    'heading',\n"
"    'footer',\n"
"])\n"
"\n"
"<div {{ $attributes->class(['border']) }}>\n"
"    <h1 {{ $heading->attributes->class(['text-lg']) }}>\n"
"        {{ $heading }}\n"
"    </h1>\n"
"\n"
"    {{ $slot }}\n"
"\n"
"    <footer {{ $footer->attributes->class(['text-gray-700']) }}>\n"
"        {{ $footer }}\n"
"    </footer>\n"
"</div>\n"
msgstr ""
