# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1133
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"building-layouts\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ##
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1132
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1133
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building Layouts"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1135
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1136
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"layouts-using-components\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ###
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1135
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Layouts Using Components"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1138
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1139
msgid "Most web applications maintain the same general layout across various pages. It would be incredibly cumbersome and hard to maintain our application if we had to repeat the entire layout HTML in every view we create. Thankfully, it's convenient to define this layout as a single [Blade component](#components) and then use it throughout our application."
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1140
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1141
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"defining-the-layout-component\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1140
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1141
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining The Layout Component"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1143
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1144
msgid "For example, imagine we are building a \"todo\" list application. We might define a `layout` component that looks like the following:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1144
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- resources/views/components/layout.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<html>\n"
"    <head>\n"
"        <title>{{ $title ?? 'Todo Manager' }}</title>\n"
"    </head>\n"
"    <body>\n"
"        <h1>Todos</h1>\n"
"        <hr/>\n"
"        {{ $slot }}\n"
"    </body>\n"
"</html>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1160
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1161
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"applying-the-layout-component\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1160
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1161
#, no-wrap
msgid "Applying The Layout Component"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1163
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1164
msgid "Once the `layout` component has been defined, we may create a Blade view that utilizes the component. In this example, we will define a simple view that displays our task list:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1164
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1165
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- resources/views/tasks.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<x-layout>\n"
"    @foreach ($tasks as $task)\n"
"        {{ $task }}\n"
"    @endforeach\n"
"</x-layout>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1175
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1176
msgid "Remember, content that is injected into a component will be supplied to the default `$slot` variable within our `layout` component. As you may have noticed, our `layout` also respects a `$title` slot if one is provided; otherwise, a default title is shown. We may inject a custom title from our task list view using the standard slot syntax discussed in the [component documentation](#components):"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1176
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- resources/views/tasks.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<x-layout>\n"
"    <x-slot name=\"title\">\n"
"        Custom Title\n"
"    </x-slot>\n"
"\n"
"    @foreach ($tasks as $task)\n"
"        {{ $task }}\n"
"    @endforeach\n"
"</x-layout>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1191
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1192
msgid "Now that we have defined our layout and task list views, we just need to return the `task` view from a route:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1193
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1194
#, no-wrap
msgid "    use App\\Models\\Task;\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1197
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Route::get('/tasks', function () {\n"
"        return view('tasks', ['tasks' => Task::all()]);\n"
"    });\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1199
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1200
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"layouts-using-template-inheritance\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ###
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1199
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1200
#, no-wrap
msgid "Layouts Using Template Inheritance"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1202
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1203
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"defining-a-layout\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1202
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1203
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining A Layout"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1205
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1206
msgid "Layouts may also be created via \"template inheritance\". This was the primary way of building applications prior to the introduction of [components](#components)."
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1207
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1208
msgid "To get started, let's take a look at a simple example. First, we will examine a page layout. Since most web applications maintain the same general layout across various pages, it's convenient to define this layout as a single Blade view:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1208
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"<html>\n"
"    <head>\n"
"        <title>App Name - @yield('title')</title>\n"
"    </head>\n"
"    <body>\n"
"        @section('sidebar')\n"
"            This is the master sidebar.\n"
"        @show\n"
"\n"
"        <div class=\"container\">\n"
"            @yield('content')\n"
"        </div>\n"
"    </body>\n"
"</html>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1228
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1229
msgid "As you can see, this file contains typical HTML mark-up. However, take note of the `@section` and `@yield` directives. The `@section` directive, as the name implies, defines a section of content, while the `@yield` directive is used to display the contents of a given section."
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1230
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1231
msgid "Now that we have defined a layout for our application, let's define a child page that inherits the layout."
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1232
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1233
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"extending-a-layout\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ####
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1232
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1233
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extending A Layout"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1235
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1236
msgid "When defining a child view, use the `@extends` Blade directive to specify which layout the child view should \"inherit\". Views which extend a Blade layout may inject content into the layout's sections using `@section` directives. Remember, as seen in the example above, the contents of these sections will be displayed in the layout using `@yield`:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1236
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1237
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<!-- resources/views/child.blade.php -->\n"
"\n"
"@extends('layouts.app')\n"
"\n"
"@section('title', 'Page Title')\n"
"\n"
"@section('sidebar')\n"
"    @@parent\n"
"\n"
"    <p>This is appended to the master sidebar.</p>\n"
"@endsection\n"
"\n"
"@section('content')\n"
"    <p>This is my body content.</p>\n"
"@endsection\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1255
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1256
msgid "In this example, the `sidebar` section is utilizing the `@@parent` directive to append (rather than overwriting) content to the layout's sidebar. The `@@parent` directive will be replaced by the content of the layout when the view is rendered."
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1257
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1258
#, no-wrap
msgid "> {tip} Contrary to the previous example, this `sidebar` section ends with `@endsection` instead of `@show`. The `@endsection` directive will only define a section while `@show` will define and **immediately yield** the section.\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1259
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1260
msgid "The `@yield` directive also accepts a default value as its second parameter. This value will be rendered if the section being yielded is undefined:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1261
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1262
#, no-wrap
msgid "    @yield('content', 'Default content')\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1263
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1264
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"forms\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ##
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1263
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1264
#, no-wrap
msgid "Forms"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1266
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1267
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"csrf-field\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ###
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1266
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1267
#, no-wrap
msgid "CSRF Field"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1269
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1270
msgid "Anytime you define an HTML form in your application, you should include a hidden CSRF token field in the form so that [the CSRF protection](/docs/{{version}}/csrf) middleware can validate the request. You may use the `@csrf` Blade directive to generate the token field:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1270
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<form method=\"POST\" action=\"/profile\">\n"
"    @csrf\n"
"\n"
"    ...\n"
"</form>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1279
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1280
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"method-field\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ###
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1279
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1280
#, no-wrap
msgid "Method Field"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1282
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1283
msgid "Since HTML forms can't make `PUT`, `PATCH`, or `DELETE` requests, you will need to add a hidden `_method` field to spoof these HTTP verbs. The `@method` Blade directive can create this field for you:"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1283
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<form action=\"/foo/bar\" method=\"POST\">\n"
"    @method('PUT')\n"
"\n"
"    ...\n"
"</form>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1292
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1293
#, no-wrap
msgid "<a name=\"validation-errors\"></a>\n"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Title ###
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1292
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1293
#, no-wrap
msgid "Validation Errors"
msgstr ""
#
#. type: Plain text
# File: docs/8.x/blade.md, line: 1295
# File: docs/master/blade.md, line: 1296
msgid "The `@error` directive may be used to quickly check if [validation error messages](/docs/{{version}}/validation#quick-displaying-the-validation-errors) exist for a given attribute. Within an `@error` directive, you may echo the `$message` variable to display the error message:"
msgstr ""
#
